This paper is about using recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for reward shaping in spoken dialogue systems. The paper discusses techniques for speeding up policy learning in these systems, which are typically trained on-line with real users. Given the focus on dialogue systems and machine learning, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SD (Sound), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
